        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 26 at 5:32PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 532 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles east of La Sal, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bedrock and Paradox.

This includes the following highways...
Colorado 90 between mile markers 4 and 17.
Colorado 141 between mile markers 76 and 101.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
